description: Natalie's Room has high ceilings, long leaf pine floors, natural light and a stunning downtown view. Tastefully decorated with a full-sized bed and family heirlooms, the entry door has a built in ringer. This room shares a bath with the Oat Willie Room. Natalie Von Schenk, the room's namesake, was one of the principals of the German-American Ladies College and lived at the school. Her sister's family and descendants lived in the house for 100 years after the school closed. Experience the century-old simplicity and ambiance of the Old School, a centrally-located historic home, whose broad, sweeping porches look out over the Austin landscape. The spacious rooms and grounds make the perfect site to host festivities. The location is easy walking distance to the Capitol, Sixth Street, restaurants like Franklin's barbeque, hip east side bars, and galleries.  A suite of three bedrooms upstairs will sleep six. description: Fully remodeled 1955 Spartan Mansion with a modern interior, expansive deck, and all the conveniences of a high end hotel.  In the center of vibrant east Austin. Walking distance to dozens of bars/eateries.  On a large landscaped lot. Very private.  This Spartan came to us in 2012 after spending 50 years untouched in a field in Mississippi.  It's interior was consumed in a fire in the late 60's.  As an homage to it's history, we finished several walls in burned cedar planks following the japanese art of Sho Sugi Ban for wood preservation.   We've spent almost 2 years completely remodeling this Spartan Royal Mansion.     The Spartan Royal Mansion is set 100ft back from the street on it's own lot making the large deck and sitting areas very private.  A large garden and a heritage chicken aviary separate it via a private path from the main house and the Spartanette.  The whole property is a rare triple lot; a little slice of homesteading in downtown. The compound is powered by solar panel
name: Modern Spartan Mansion Guesthouse

description: Come stay at our quiet, art-filled modern home in East Austin!  This private bedroom (located on the 2nd floor) gets great natural light and has a bathroom that will only be used by you—plus there's a fantastic deck right outside the room. We're a 15-minute drive from downtown, UT, the airport, Carson Creek Ranch, McKinney Falls State Park, the Domain, and the Circuit of the Americas. This is the perfect place to stay if you're looking for a quiet retreat that's just a little bit away from the craziness of the city without being inconvenient.  The room is in a modern, light-filled home that has almost 40 windows. It's located on a quiet cul-de-sac in a really unique, award-winning, all-modern neighborhood called Agave.  Note that we have a cat: a Maine Coon named Sammy who you'll probably see napping while lying on his back in various spots downstairs. The guest room has bamboo floors, a remote-controlled ceiling fan with a dimmable light, and 2 twin XL beds with memory foam mattresses
name: Modern private room with deck!
